## Cross-Phase Dependencies

### Depends On (Phase 6)
- Dashboard foundation: Next.js app router, `withAuth` wrapper, SWR data fetching.
- API route structure and conventions.

### Depends On (Phase 8)
- Auto-rollback system: when crash-loop detection triggers a rollback, it should call `notify()`.
- `rollbackDeployment()` function exists in `packages/core/src/deploy/rollback.ts`.

### Depends On (Phase 4 & 5)
- `BuildRunner.run()` has failure paths where notifications should be sent.
- `Deployer.deploy()` has failure paths (health check failure, container start failure).

### Depends On (Phase 3)
- GitHub App installation info (for the settings page connection status display).
- `GITHUB_APP_ID` and installation ID available for querying the GitHub API.

### Enables
- This is the final phase. It makes the platform production-ready with observability.

---

## Risk & Mitigation

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|--------|------------|
| Slack/Discord webhook URL invalid or expired | Medium | Low | Validate URL format; test button; graceful error handling |
| Notification spam during rapid deployments | Low | Medium | Debounce: don't send more than 1 notification per project per 5 minutes for the same event type |
| VPS monitoring command execution timeout | Low | Low | Set 5-second timeout on `exec` commands; return stale data on timeout |
| Shell command injection in VPS monitor | Low | High | No user input in shell commands; all commands are hardcoded |
| Settings page performance with frequent VPS stat polling | Low | Low | Poll every 30s; use SWR's `refreshInterval`; abort on page navigation |

